no-reserved-keys.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at eliminating the use of ECMAScript 3 keywords and reserved words as object literal keys. As such, it warns whenever an object key would throw an error in an ECMAScript 3 environment.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

var superman = {
    class: "Superhero",
    private: "Clark Kent"
};

var values = {
    enum: ["red", "blue", "green"]
};

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

var superman = {
    "class": "Superhero",
    "private": "Clark Kent"
};

var values = {
    "enum": ["red", "blue", "green"]
};
